-- French Business Confidence Rises to Highest in Five Months in September
-- B y   G r e g o r y   V i s c u s i
-- 2010-10-08T06:30:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-08/franch-business-confidence-rises-to-highest-in-five-months-in-september.html
French business confidence rose in
September as industrial production picked up.  The  Bank of France’s Business Sentiment Indicator  for
manufacturers gained to 102 in September, after holding at 101
for the previous five months, the Paris-based central bank said
today in a statement.  Capacity utilization at French factories rose to 76.8
percent in September from 74.4 percent in August.  “Capacity utilization rose significantly but remained
below its long term average,” the central bank said in the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Gregory Viscusi  in Paris at 
 gviscusi@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at 
 jhertling@bloomberg.net . 